init_text:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The solution is to listen to books.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This is a service provided by the National Library Service for the Blind and Physically Handicapped.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It is a free service to the blind and visually impaired.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The service is provided by volunteers who read books into a recording device.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The result is that the books are read in a monotone voice.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The solution to this problem is to use a professional reader.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: However, in the last 20 years, the number of books available in audiobook format has increased dramatically.
